{"id":8465,"title":"[Bovine viral diarrhea control in Russian Federation].","abstract":"Bovine viral diarrhea (BVD) is one of the greatest challenges for breeding and commercial livestock. It is characterized by lesions of the respiratory and gastrointestinal tract, abortion, infertility, immune deficiency, and persistence of the pathogen. In this work, a set of measures for the rehabilitation and prevention of BVD in cattle is described. It includes the data of the literature, guidance documents for the diagnosis and control of BVD adopted by OIE, EU countries, USA, as well as the results of this research.","date":"2014-04-29","categories":"Animal Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24772640","annotations":[{"name":"Abortion","weight":0.811048,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abortion"},{"name":"Human gastrointestinal tract","weight":0.810247,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_gastrointestinal_tract"},{"name":"Diarrhea","weight":0.804517,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diarrhea"},{"name":"Pathogen","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogen"},{"name":"Immunodeficiency","weight":0.723778,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunodeficiency"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.676635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Virus","weight":0.665477,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virus"},{"name":"Respiratory system","weight":0.663387,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Respiratory_system"},{"name":"Russia","weight":0.657436,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia"},{"name":"Infertility","weight":0.643326,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infertility"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.633471,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Livestock","weight":0.54985,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Livestock"},{"n